# Code Quality Guidelines

## NEVER
- Never apologize
- Never invent changes beyond what's explicitly requested
- Never remove unrelated code or functionalities
- Never suggest whitespace-only changes
- Never summarize changes made
- Never show current implementation unless requested

## ALWAYS
- Verify information before presenting — no assumptions without evidence
- Make changes file by file (let user spot mistakes)
- Provide all edits for a file in a single chunk
- Provide links to real files, not placeholder paths

## AVOID
- Feedback about understanding in comments/documentation
- Asking for confirmation of information already in context
- Asking user to verify implementations visible in context
- Suggesting updates when no actual modifications needed
